Just no need to rush it.

199
00:10:53,015 --> 00:10:55,017
No need to be so thirsty, Veronica.

200
00:11:06,434 --> 00:11:08,101
I'm off to school. Here.

201
00:11:08,103 --> 00:11:10,855
- What's that?
- I don't know. It was on the porch.

202
00:11:13,942 --> 00:11:15,902
Guys, we're under attack.

203
00:11:17,328 --> 00:11:20,206
And by "we," I mean our
friends, our families.

204
00:11:21,491 --> 00:11:23,368
This time, it was Moose and Midge.

205
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:28,297
Next time, it could be you...
your girlfriend, your family.

206
00:11:29,124 --> 00:11:31,126
It's time to do something about it.

207
00:11:32,085 --> 00:11:34,168
I want us to start a watch group.

208
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:37,015
Not to canvass the town,
that's not workable,

209
00:11:37,018 --> 00:11:40,008
but to focus on Riverdale
High, its students,

210
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:42,302
its faculty and staff, its parents,

211
00:11:42,304 --> 00:11:45,788
where we all hang out, an extra
circle of protection around it.

212
00:11:45,791 --> 00:11:49,809
You want us to take it to
the streets, kick some ass.

213
00:11:49,811 --> 00:11:55,648
That was my first thought, too, Reg.
But no, no weapons, no violence.

214
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:59,736
I'm talking about a patrol, an extra
set of eyes and ears for the police.

215
00:11:59,738 --> 00:12:01,781
And what if we run into the killer?

216
00:12:05,368 --> 00:12:06,995
Then we call Sheriff Keller.

217
00:12:07,662 --> 00:12:10,054
We're not vigilantes. We're watchdogs.

218
00:12:10,057 --> 00:12:13,968
- We're the Watchdogs.
- We're not called the Watchdogs, Reg.

219
00:12:15,295 --> 00:12:16,838
We're called the Red Circle.

220
00:12:17,788 --> 00:12:19,007
We hold the line.

221
00:12:19,633 --> 00:12:23,259
We're not waiting for the next
attack. We're protecting our own.

222
00:12:23,261 --> 00:12:26,163
- Whoo! Yeah.
- Yeah. Yeah.

