Let's start with the title.

227
00:12:37,434 --> 00:12:39,476
Can anyone tell me its significance?

228
00:12:39,479 --> 00:12:41,029
What? Damn it!

229
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:49,621
People, there's a
burning book on the cover.

230
00:12:54,084 --> 00:12:57,545
Fahrenheit 451 is the
temperature at which paper burns.

231
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:02,342
"It was a pleasure to burn."

232
00:13:03,593 --> 00:13:04,842
Indeed.

233
00:13:04,844 --> 00:13:09,891
Thank you, Mr... Jones.
And welcome to hell.

234
00:13:11,476 --> 00:13:12,852
[BELL RINGS]

235
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:20,692
Uh, hi, Mr. Phillips?

236
00:13:20,694 --> 00:13:22,610
[PHILLIPS] Mr. Jones.

237
00:13:22,612 --> 00:13:25,710
Toni was telling me you used
to advise the school paper.

238
00:13:25,713 --> 00:13:27,548
I was wondering what happened.

239
00:13:29,429 --> 00:13:32,226
Drugs and gangs came to Southside High.

240
00:13:33,163 --> 00:13:36,265
Trying to get students
interested in the school paper

241
00:13:36,268 --> 00:13:38,584
was an exercise in futility.

242
00:13:38,586 --> 00:13:40,186
I'm interested. I have experience.

243
00:13:40,189 --> 00:13:43,300
At Riverdale High, I wrote
for the <i>Blue and Gold.</i>

244
00:13:43,303 --> 00:13:45,510
I'll put in the work.

245
00:13:47,511 --> 00:13:49,301
Your articles online?

246
00:13:49,304 --> 00:13:50,596
Mm-hm.

247
00:13:50,598 --> 00:13:52,660
I'll take a look, let you know.

248
00:13:52,663 --> 00:13:53,935
[JUGHEAD] Thanks.

249
00:13:57,981 --> 00:14:00,732
Hey. What happened last night?

250
00:14:00,734 --> 00:14:02,567
You said you were coming to Veronica's.

251
00:14:02,569 --> 00:14:03,945
Yeah, something came up.

252
00:14:06,072 --> 00:14:07,780
Something in the woods?

253
00:14:07,782 --> 00:14:09,907
Betty, don't take this the wrong way,

254
00:14:09,909 --> 00:14:14,470
but how many years did I listen to
you go on about Archie and Jughead?

255
00:14:14,473 --> 00:14:16,807
Did you ask my permission to date them?

256
00:14:16,810 --> 00:14:19,477
No. You didn't need it.
And I don't need yours.

257
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:23,463
- [BETTY] Dating is one thing. This is...
- It's none of your business.

258
00:14:23,465 --> 00:14:25,298
I'll, uh, catch you later.

259
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:26,468
Kev. [SCOFFS]

260
00:14:29,929 --> 00:14:34,642
So, button-down Kevin Keller
has a sex-drive. So what?

261
00:14:35,685 --> 00:14:40,212
So, it's putting him in
danger. Why won't he just stop?

262
00:14:40,215 --> 00:14:43,610
Oh, Betty. How little you
know of the human psyche.

263
00:14:44,611 --> 00:14:48,239
Kevin used to be a lonely,
awkward fat boy with acne.

264
00:14:49,064 --> 00:14:50,575
Now he's a smoke-show.

265
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:52,492
And?

266
00:14:52,494 --> 00:14:56,037
In his mind, he's still
that unattractive Pugsley.

267
00:14:56,039 --> 00:15:01,086
Kevin wants validation, connection,
even if he has to find it in the woods.

268
00:15:01,753 --> 00:15:05,256
Even with a killer on the
loose. Even if you don't approve.

269
00:15:10,553 --> 00:15:12,970
[VERONICA] <i>I have
incredible news, Archiekins.</i>

270
00:15:12,972 --> 00:15:16,267
You are invited to dinner with
my parents, <i>chez moi.</i>

271
00:15:17,268 --> 00:15:20,019
- Oh, Ronnie, this week's crazy...
- I don't care.

272
00:15:20,021 --> 00:15:22,271
Archie, this is nonnegotiable.

273
00:15:22,273 --> 00:15:25,441
That drive-by he did
was a kind gesture,

274
00:15:25,443 --> 00:15:30,321
but this, this is like... I don't wanna
call it a test, though it kind of is.

275
00:15:30,323 --> 00:15:33,616
- What am I being tested for?
- Not you, my father.

276
00:15:33,618 --> 00:15:35,952
Can he just be a dad for one night?

277
00:15:35,954 --> 00:15:40,583
No agenda other than getting to
know someone who's important to me.

278
00:15:42,043 --> 00:15:46,546
- In that case, I'll be there for you.
- I don't have time to teach you Spanish,

279
00:15:46,548 --> 00:15:49,841
but I've selected phrases for
you to memorize and practice.

280
00:15:49,843 --> 00:15:53,843
And can we not talk about that
private army you're starting? Okay?

281
00:15:53,846 --> 00:15:55,265
Thanks.

282
00:16:03,143 --> 00:16:04,482
[BETTY] Hey.

283
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:07,569
- Hey. [SIGHS]
- [BETTY] What's wrong?

284
00:16:09,886 --> 00:16:12,053
Your mother got some fan mail.

285
00:16:12,056 --> 00:16:16,411
He calls himself the Black Hood and
he wants us to publish this letter.

286
00:16:16,414 --> 00:16:18,502
He wants everyone to know

287
00:16:18,505 --> 00:16:21,830
that he shot Fred Andrews
and Moose and Midge...

288
00:16:22,506 --> 00:16:24,381
and murdered Geraldine Grundy.

289
00:16:24,384 --> 00:16:26,801
Are you sure that this is real?

290
00:16:26,804 --> 00:16:28,389
[ALICE] Oh, it's real, all right.

291
00:16:39,952 --> 00:16:41,868
[KELLER] "This is the Black Hood.

292
00:16:41,893 --> 00:16:45,408
I am the man who shot
the adulterer at Pop's.

293
00:16:47,026 --> 00:16:49,904
<i>I killed the child predator in Greendale.</i>

294
00:16:50,529 --> 00:16:54,990
<i>I shot the drug- and sex-addicted
teenagers at Lovers' Lane.</i>

295
00:16:54,992 --> 00:16:56,700
<i>Riverdale is not innocent.</i>

296
00:16:56,702 --> 00:17:00,706
<i>It's a town of hypocrites,
degenerates, criminals.</i>

297
00:17:02,124 --> 00:17:08,589
<i>My wrath is the price of your
lies, your secrets, your sins.</i>

298
00:17:09,298 --> 00:17:13,093
<i>I will not stop. I cannot be stopped.</i>

299
00:17:13,886 --> 00:17:16,972
<i>I am the wolf. You are the flock.</i>

300
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:21,227
This is the blood-letting.
You will hear from me again."

301
00:17:21,894 --> 00:17:24,269
Well, Tom, how real is this threat?

302
00:17:24,271 --> 00:17:26,815
Well, it's definitely
Fred Andrews' wallet.

303
00:17:27,691 --> 00:17:30,361
These sunglasses, I'm
checking with Greendale P.D.

304
00:17:32,196 --> 00:17:37,366
Alice, in the spirit of public
safety... Tom, tell me if you disagree.

305
00:17:37,368 --> 00:17:40,410
It's important to not give
this lunatic an audience.

306
00:17:40,412 --> 00:17:44,315
Mayor McCoy, it is our responsibility
to let the public know he's out there

307
00:17:44,318 --> 00:17:46,659
targeting his next victim.

308
00:17:46,662 --> 00:17:50,254
If you print this,
you're gonna cause panic.

309
00:17:50,256 --> 00:17:54,383
I want a media blackout for 24
hours on this letter, at least.

310
00:17:54,385 --> 00:17:56,635
And I'll be taking it into Evidence.

311
00:17:56,637 --> 00:17:58,178
I'll send you a copy.

312
00:17:58,180 --> 00:17:59,721
[ALICE] Oh, no need, sheriff.

313
00:17:59,723 --> 00:18:02,015
We made one right before
we sent it to the printer

314
00:18:02,017 --> 00:18:03,686
for tomorrow's front page.

315
00:18:05,187 --> 00:18:09,398
Mr. Jones, I read your
work. I'm impressed.

316
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:12,565
So much so that I'll consider
reopening the <i>Red and the Black</i>

317
00:18:12,568 --> 00:18:13,651
on two conditions:

318
00:18:13,654 --> 00:18:16,530
One, no gangs. Two, no jingle-jangle.

319
00:18:16,533 --> 00:18:19,867
Write about them. If I see you
trafficking in either, we're done.

320
00:18:19,870 --> 00:18:21,831
That will not be a problem for me.

321
00:18:25,791 --> 00:18:28,669
Did you think I'd let
teenagers form a militia?

322
00:18:29,378 --> 00:18:31,420
We're trying to help, sheriff.

323
00:18:31,422 --> 00:18:34,172
- People are scared.
- A lynch mob won't help that.

324
00:18:34,174 --> 00:18:37,217
- Sheriff Keller.
- We have a big problem here, Waldo.

325
00:18:37,219 --> 00:18:40,514
You see, your student has
formed his own private army.

326
00:18:41,682 --> 00:18:43,517
The Red Circle is a school club.

327
00:18:44,143 --> 00:18:45,726
You endorse this?

328
00:18:45,728 --> 00:18:48,103
[WEATHERBEE] Archie has
shown tremendous initiative.

329
00:18:48,105 --> 00:18:51,442
You can't fault students for
wanting to protect each other.

330
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:55,070
Morning, Waldo.

331
00:18:58,949 --> 00:19:00,326
[ARCHIE CHUCKLES]

332
00:19:03,659 --> 00:19:04,997
[COUGHS]

333
00:19:07,499 --> 00:19:09,167
Well, it's no <i>New York Times.</i>

334
00:19:09,951 --> 00:19:13,286
But, hey, kudos on finding
your safe space, snowflake.

335
00:19:13,297 --> 00:19:17,674
Yeah, all I need now is a
photographer with an amazing eye

336
00:19:17,676 --> 00:19:20,093
and a hunger for social justice,

337
00:19:20,095 --> 00:19:21,513
and I think I'll be set.

338
00:19:22,948 --> 00:19:24,224
[DOOR OPENS]

339
00:19:25,317 --> 00:19:27,319
Topaz. Let's bounce.

340
00:19:29,355 --> 00:19:32,272
Jones, wanna come with?
We're going to the quarry.

341
00:19:32,274 --> 00:19:35,108
Uh, I don't have my beach bod yet.

342
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:39,479
What? You'll ask for help from the
Serpents, but you won't hang with us?

343
00:19:39,482 --> 00:19:41,732
Don't come crawling to us, hat in hand,

344
00:19:41,735 --> 00:19:45,862
when some Ghoulie decides to earn his
stripes by taking out FP Jones' kid.

345
00:19:45,865 --> 00:19:48,409
Duly noted. Thank you, Sweet Pea.

346
00:19:49,778 --> 00:19:53,908
I appreciate what you and the Serpents
have done for me and my dad. I do.

347
00:19:55,242 --> 00:19:57,494
But I'm done. Okay?

348
00:19:58,738 --> 00:20:00,740
No more favors coming your way.

349
00:20:02,179 --> 00:20:04,515
Hey, hey, he made up his mind, okay?

350
00:20:05,182 --> 00:20:08,602
Take the hint, Sweet Pea.
He's just not that into you.

351
00:20:09,221 --> 00:20:10,562
Let's motor.

352
00:20:13,023 --> 00:20:14,400
Catch you later, Jones.

353
00:20:19,154 --> 00:20:23,198
- I'm going. I'm leaving Riverdale.
- You'll give the babies whiplash.

354
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:25,495
[POLLY] I've called the
farm. They still have room.

355
00:20:25,498 --> 00:20:26,488
Farm? What farm?

356
00:20:26,491 --> 00:20:29,651
The farm Jason and I were running
to before my life fell apart.

357
00:20:29,654 --> 00:20:33,495
Honey, let's just talk about
this. Why are you leaving?

358
00:20:33,498 --> 00:20:36,166
Ask Mom. She's the one baiting a killer.

359
00:20:36,169 --> 00:20:39,596
- A killer targeting sinners.
- Polly, you're not a sinner.

360
00:20:39,599 --> 00:20:42,308
I'm an unwed mother
carrying my cousin's babies.

361
00:20:42,311 --> 00:20:44,269
I am the poster child for sin.

362
00:20:44,272 --> 00:20:48,305
That's it. Over my dead body are
you gonna run off to some farm

363
00:20:48,308 --> 00:20:50,642
and give birth in a trough, no doubt.

364
00:20:50,644 --> 00:20:52,448
It might be over your dead body, Mother,

365
00:20:52,451 --> 00:20:55,037
but it won't be over mine or my babies'.

366
00:20:56,574 --> 00:20:57,698
Polly!

367
00:20:57,701 --> 00:20:58,785
I'll talk to her.

368
00:21:07,318 --> 00:21:11,487
Midge wanted to thank
you... for saving my life.

369
00:21:11,498 --> 00:21:12,789
[SCOFFS]

370
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:14,501
You're like her new hero now.

371
00:21:16,628 --> 00:21:17,711
[SIGHS]

372
00:21:17,713 --> 00:21:21,800
Hey, so, what were you doing
out there in the woods, anyways?

373
00:21:23,302 --> 00:21:27,096
[CHUCKLES] What were you doing out
there with Midge? Besides drugs.

374
00:21:27,099 --> 00:21:31,226
That was her idea. She likes
to get a little crazy sometimes.

375
00:21:34,438 --> 00:21:37,024
I like Midge, a lot.

376
00:21:37,824 --> 00:21:40,869
Sometimes I'm not sure
we're that great a match.

377
00:21:42,571 --> 00:21:45,324
Kevin, are you okay?

378
00:21:46,241 --> 00:21:48,815
I haven't been making
great decisions lately.

379
00:21:48,818 --> 00:21:52,578
Lying to my dad, sneaking
around and going into the woods.

380
00:21:52,581 --> 00:21:55,290
I know it's dangerous,
but I can't stop myself.

381
00:21:55,292 --> 00:21:57,794
It's like I don't even
care. What is that?

382
00:21:58,595 --> 00:22:01,556
I don't know, but guys like us?

383
00:22:02,508 --> 00:22:03,753
Like you?

384
00:22:04,551 --> 00:22:06,220
In a town like Riverdale?

385
00:22:07,562 --> 00:22:09,564
We don't have a lot of options.

386
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:15,935
So, even if something bad
could happen, we go for it,

387
00:22:15,938 --> 00:22:19,066
'cause what if for ten minutes...

388
00:22:19,983 --> 00:22:23,946
or maybe even just for two
minutes... we're not alone?

389
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:28,283
[CHUCKLES] I'm glad you're
okay, Moose. Midge, too.

390
00:22:30,675 --> 00:22:31,870
Kevin.

391
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,412
You don't have to go.

392
00:22:34,414 --> 00:22:36,917
Or you can come back, whenever.

393
00:22:37,709 --> 00:22:40,629
If you wanna hang out... or talk.

394
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:51,763
You're playing with
fire, I want you to know.

395
00:22:51,765 --> 00:22:54,099
I'm polishing cutlery, Mom.

396
00:22:54,101 --> 00:22:57,855
In advance of my parents getting
to know my boyfriend over dinner.

397
00:22:57,858 --> 00:23:01,597
That may be your agenda, but it's
not necessarily your father's.

398
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:04,401
He's making an effort,
I'm making an effort.

399
00:23:04,403 --> 00:23:06,371
The only person not
making an effort is you.

400
00:23:06,374 --> 00:23:09,531
- I'm trying to warn you.
- About what, Mom?

401
00:23:09,533 --> 00:23:11,700
What do you think Daddy's gonna do?

402
00:23:11,702 --> 00:23:14,535
Please, God, enough of
these veiled threats.

403
00:23:14,538 --> 00:23:16,705
Tell me you think he's dangerous.

404
00:23:16,707 --> 00:23:19,291
Say it to my face or
forever hold your peace

405
00:23:19,293 --> 00:23:22,087
because we're never having
this conversation again.

406
00:23:26,925 --> 00:23:28,427
Can't do it, can you?

407
00:23:32,339 --> 00:23:36,300
Just remember, you're the
one who welcomed him back.

408
00:23:36,303 --> 00:23:37,470
[SCOFFS]

409
00:23:45,346 --> 00:23:47,348
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO]

410
00:23:50,933 --> 00:23:54,478
- Huh. I thought no weapons.
- I've had this bat since I was 10.

411
00:23:56,223 --> 00:23:57,599
Check out the backseat.

412
00:23:59,003 --> 00:24:00,234
Old-school.

413
00:24:06,511 --> 00:24:07,792
[DOOR OPENS]

414
00:24:09,744 --> 00:24:10,826
Oh...

415
00:24:10,828 --> 00:24:13,162
- [JUGHEAD] Betty.
- So, this is the <i>Red and Black.</i>

416
00:24:13,164 --> 00:24:16,209
You cannot be here at
night unless you are armed.

417
00:24:17,251 --> 00:24:19,379
Well, I am.

418
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,422
[CHUCKLES]

419
00:24:22,340 --> 00:24:25,266
Okay, honestly? I hit pay dirt.

420
00:24:25,269 --> 00:24:27,093
Do you remember how
no one could explain

421
00:24:27,095 --> 00:24:29,970
the local component of Clifford
Blossom's drug pipeline?

422
00:24:29,972 --> 00:24:34,767
That jingle-jangle, the stuff Moose and
Midge were on? It's coming from here.

423
00:24:34,769 --> 00:24:39,563
My dad said that Serpents never deal
in hard drugs, but the Ghoulies do.

424
00:24:39,565 --> 00:24:41,857
Well, is it wise to be writing

425
00:24:41,859 --> 00:24:45,699
about gangs and drugs while
you're going to school here?

426
00:24:45,702 --> 00:24:47,156
You worried about me?

427
00:24:48,783 --> 00:24:50,576
Well, yeah, Jug.

428
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:54,872
I thought you liked me reckless.

429
00:25:02,230 --> 00:25:03,921
[DOOR CREAKS]

430
00:25:03,923 --> 00:25:07,341
Oh, sorry, guys. I didn't
see the sock on the door.

431
00:25:07,343 --> 00:25:08,970
It's okay. Heh.

432
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:12,471
Hey, Toni. Ah...

433
00:25:12,473 --> 00:25:15,474
Betty, this is Toni. She is the
photographer for the newspaper.

434
00:25:15,476 --> 00:25:16,675
Oh.

435
00:25:16,678 --> 00:25:20,187
- This is Betty. This is my girlfriend.
- [BETTY] Hi, Toni.

436
00:25:20,189 --> 00:25:24,972
- Huh. You are not at all what I pictured.
- Really? What did you picture?

437
00:25:24,975 --> 00:25:26,944
[TONI] Uh, Emily the Strange.

438
00:25:26,946 --> 00:25:28,739
Winona Ryder from <i>Beetlejuice.</i>

439
00:25:31,951 --> 00:25:33,619
Hey, look what Betty got us.

440
00:25:36,239 --> 00:25:37,532
Great minds.

441
00:25:39,083 --> 00:25:40,293
Great minds.

442
00:25:43,753 --> 00:25:46,796
Well. Perfect timing. Zip me up?

443
00:25:46,799 --> 00:25:48,011
Of course.

444
00:25:49,510 --> 00:25:53,806
You know, the one thing about this
apartment is that sound carries.

445
00:25:55,315 --> 00:25:59,319
Even in my study, I could hear you
and Veronica in the dining room...

446
00:26:00,813 --> 00:26:02,315
as if we're all together.

447
00:26:05,234 --> 00:26:07,558
If you wanna burn your
relationship with our daughter,

448
00:26:07,561 --> 00:26:09,069
that's your business.

449
00:26:09,071 --> 00:26:12,366
But... don't ever try
to poison her against me.

450
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:15,244
Clear?

451
00:26:16,829 --> 00:26:18,080
- Of course.
- Yeah.

452
00:26:19,590 --> 00:26:20,791
You look nice.

453
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:30,174
[ON JUKEBOX] <i>♪ Close
your eyes, now, baby ♪</i>

454
00:26:30,176 --> 00:26:32,843
- [KEVIN] Thank you, Delores.
- [DELORES] Anytime.

455
00:26:32,845 --> 00:26:34,222
Have a good run, Kevin.

456
00:26:37,808 --> 00:26:39,810
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES]

457
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:48,270
Oh, Kevin.

458
00:26:48,273 --> 00:26:52,782
You precious, beautiful,
compulsive piece of trash.

459
00:27:44,542 --> 00:27:46,333
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO]

460
00:27:46,335 --> 00:27:48,337
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

461
00:27:51,257 --> 00:27:52,883
Hey, this is Archie.

462
00:27:53,843 --> 00:27:57,013
Okay, slow down. I can
barely... Are you sure?

463
00:27:58,298 --> 00:28:01,716
No, don't. Don't do that.
Just get somewhere safe, okay?

464
00:28:01,719 --> 00:28:04,928
Turn back to Hastings Street.
Stay calm. We're on our way.

465
00:28:04,931 --> 00:28:06,892
